1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:07,924
[rock guitar riff playing]

2
00:00:08,591 --> 00:00:13,930
Pulled over by the cops 20 minutes after
we gave you the Vista Cruiser?

3
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:16,766
Who could have pulled off
something like that?

4
00:00:17,350 --> 00:00:22,063
Only a criminal mastermind
without the mind.

5
00:00:24,065 --> 00:00:25,233
A Kelso.

6
00:00:26,484 --> 00:00:28,445
Trouble just follows them, honey.

7
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:31,031
They're like those frogs
in the rainforest.

8
00:00:31,114 --> 00:00:32,240
Colorful and pretty,

9
00:00:32,323 --> 00:00:35,702
but if you lick them,
all your skin falls off and you die.

10
00:00:36,411 --> 00:00:38,621
I'm sorry, but can we just stop
for a second?

11
00:00:38,705 --> 00:00:41,499
Because how cute is this
that we are holding hands? [chuckles]

12
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:43,376
It finally happened, you guys!

13
00:00:44,669 --> 00:00:47,797
Grandpa, I know this looks bad,
but we only got pulled over

14
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:50,300
because the car had
license plates from 1980.

15
00:00:50,383 --> 00:00:52,052
She's right, Mr. Forman.

16
00:00:52,135 --> 00:00:54,846
Sometimes, if you're searching for blame,

17
00:00:54,929 --> 00:00:56,264
it's best to look inward.

18
00:00:56,973 --> 00:00:59,809
My foot's about to go inward your ass.

19
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:03,104
You can't set him up like that.

20
00:01:03,605 --> 00:01:06,274
I know we're off to a rough start,
but give me a chance.

21
00:01:06,357 --> 00:01:09,694
Someday, this frog
is gonna turn into a butterfly.

22
00:01:10,653 --> 00:01:12,822
I'm getting stupider standing here.

23
00:01:14,324 --> 00:01:17,202
You are banned from this house. Get out.

24
00:01:17,285 --> 00:01:18,536
What? No!

25
00:01:20,497 --> 00:01:22,123
Honey. Honey.

26
00:01:22,207 --> 00:01:23,416
Let go of the frog.

27
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,002
-[rock music playing]
-<i>One, two, three, four!</i>

28
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:27,837
<i>♪ Hangin' out down the street ♪</i>

29
00:01:27,921 --> 00:01:29,923
<i>♪ The same old thing we did last week ♪</i>

30
00:01:30,006 --> 00:01:32,258
<i>♪ Not a thing to do ♪</i>

31
00:01:32,342 --> 00:01:34,344
<i>♪ But talk to you ♪</i>

32
00:01:34,427 --> 00:01:35,470
<i>♪ We're all all right! ♪</i>

33
00:01:35,553 --> 00:01:37,055
<i>♪ We're all all right! ♪</i>

34
00:01:37,138 --> 00:01:39,682
[young woman] <i>Hello, Wisconsin!</i>

35
00:01:40,725 --> 00:01:41,810
The Kool-Aid Man?

36
00:01:42,477 --> 00:01:44,104
<i>That's</i> the tattoo you wanna get?

37
00:01:44,187 --> 00:01:45,855
The key is to not overthink it.

38
00:01:46,439 --> 00:01:47,690
Mission accomplished.

39
00:01:48,399 --> 00:01:52,028
Jay, I miss you, and I feel so bad
you can't be here for all the fun.

40
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:53,822
Gwen and Ozzie are talking.

41
00:01:53,905 --> 00:01:55,323
Nikki's chewing gum.

42
00:01:55,824 --> 00:01:57,534
And Nate's adjusting his junk.

43
00:01:57,617 --> 00:01:59,077
You need more powder, babe.

44
00:01:59,869 --> 00:02:02,038
Summer's the worst season for your junk.

45
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:04,040
Hey. Can I talk to him?

46
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:07,085
Just come over, bro.

47
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:09,462
Leia's grandma's at the dentist.
Red's stuck at the DMV.

48
00:02:10,421 --> 00:02:11,548
Damn it. I miss you too.

49
00:02:13,007 --> 00:02:14,801
-He's coming over.
-He is?

50
00:02:14,884 --> 00:02:16,427
I gotta shave my pits!

51
00:02:16,511 --> 00:02:17,762
[Jay] <i>Uh, what?</i>

52
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:19,889
[nervous chuckle] That was Nikki. Bye!

53
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:22,725
Gwen. Help me.

54
00:02:24,519 --> 00:02:25,770
Boyfriend, day one.

55
00:02:26,396 --> 00:02:27,897
Oh, I gotta take off too.

56
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:30,066
I'm meeting my SAT tutor in 20 minutes.

57
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:31,192
Again with that guy?

58
00:02:31,276 --> 00:02:34,863
But you're already so smart.
You helped me escape from that trampoline.

59
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:39,242
Babe, I need to ace the SATs,
get into a good college, cure a disease,

60
00:02:39,325 --> 00:02:41,995
and have my face on a stamp
so my enemies can lick it.

61
00:02:46,457 --> 00:02:48,710
She's spending a lot of time
with that tutor guy.

62
00:02:48,793 --> 00:02:50,170
Is someone feeling jealous?

63
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:51,963
No, I am.

64
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:55,884
I mean, she's with this guy all the time.

65
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:58,928
Do you think I have
anything to worry about?

66
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:03,141
Tough to answer without knowing
who the guy is, but, knowing you,

67
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:05,143
maybe.

68
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:07,353
I know, right?

69
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:09,647
If it's really bothering you,
let's check this guy out.

70
00:03:10,523 --> 00:03:12,233
Nah, I should just trust her.

71
00:03:12,317 --> 00:03:16,863
Nate, I watch a lot of talk shows,
and I've learned two things.

72
00:03:17,614 --> 00:03:18,531
People cheat.

73
00:03:19,032 --> 00:03:21,201
And once a ho, always a ho.

74
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:24,204
[rock music playing]

75
00:03:26,956 --> 00:03:27,957
I'm so happy you're here.

76
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:31,920
It's gonna be okay.
Take three steps forward.

77
00:03:32,003 --> 00:03:33,463
I can't. What if Red comes home?

78
00:03:33,546 --> 00:03:35,381
He is just being smart, Gwen.

79
00:03:35,465 --> 00:03:37,550
Smart and hot and brave.

80
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:40,803
-I'm not scared of somebody's grandpa.
-[coughs]

81
00:03:40,887 --> 00:03:42,180
-[Jay yells]
-[Sherri shrieks]

82
00:03:42,263 --> 00:03:44,182
Holy hell! I was just
trying to scooch by ya,

83
00:03:44,265 --> 00:03:48,102
not scare the Milk Duds
out of all of us. [exclaims]

84
00:03:48,186 --> 00:03:50,480
Hi, Ms. Runck.
Sorry, but my grandma's not home.

85
00:03:50,563 --> 00:03:53,858
I know. I gotta pick her up at the dentist
soon because she's gonna be zonked.

86
00:03:53,942 --> 00:03:56,736
But I thought I'd pop over first
and do a little grocery shoppin'.

87
00:03:56,819 --> 00:03:59,572
So much easier than going
all the way down to the store, ya know?

88
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:00,990
Mom!

89
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:03,701
-Grab me some yogurts.
-Oh.

90
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:07,080
Oh, you know it's the beginning
of a relationship

91
00:04:07,163 --> 00:04:09,415
when the guy still goes outside
to cut the cheese.

92
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,293
Jay, just come in.

93
00:04:13,211 --> 00:04:15,421
-I missed you so much.
-Missed you too.

94
00:04:15,505 --> 00:04:17,298
What? He just get back
from Iraq or something?

95
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:21,469
They've been apart for one day.
Her grandpa banned him from the house.

96
00:04:21,552 --> 00:04:24,097
Sounds like Red's being
a hard-ass like my dad.

97
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:25,932
He never believed in me.

98
00:04:26,015 --> 00:04:28,268
Sometimes I wonder
if that might've screwed me up.

99
00:04:28,351 --> 00:04:29,352
No.

100
00:04:30,895 --> 00:04:32,897
Aw, that's nice, hon,
but I really think he did.

101
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:37,193
The point is, adults should be
more understanding. You know?

102
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:40,488
I mean, just throwing rules out at kids
is not the answer.

103
00:04:40,571 --> 00:04:42,490
So you'll sign off on me getting a tattoo?

104
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:43,866
Sorry, lady.

105
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:46,411
I'm fine with you making mistakes,
but not permanent ones.

106
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:49,831
Tattoos, babies, and DUIs,
the unholy trinity.

107
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:52,667
Wait, isn't the dentist
like five minutes away?

108
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:54,794
Jay, why don't <i>we </i>go pick up my grandma?

109
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:57,338
I know this isn't
the sexiest thing I've ever said,

110
00:04:58,089 --> 00:04:59,966
but I'm pretty sure
your grandpa can kick my ass.

111
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:03,720
But it would show him
how responsible you are.

112
00:05:03,803 --> 00:05:06,264
Yeah, and while you're at it,
you gotta let Red know

113
00:05:06,347 --> 00:05:08,141
that you're tired of him judging ya.

114
00:05:08,224 --> 00:05:12,103
And still, to this day,
making you feel unworthy, disrespected,

115
00:05:12,186 --> 00:05:14,022
and like you're not a good mom!

116
00:05:15,606 --> 00:05:17,692
I feel like that wasn't all about us.

117
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:19,902
We have to try something.

118
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:21,154
Can we borrow your car?

119
00:05:21,654 --> 00:05:23,781
Don't know if I should get
between you and your grandpa.

120
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:26,409
-We'll fill it up with gas.
-Here's my keys.

121
00:05:27,452 --> 00:05:29,871
I'll stay here
and finish up my grocery shopping.

122
00:05:31,122 --> 00:05:33,082
I know you're worried,
but all we have to do

123
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:34,876
is pick up my sweet, sedated grandma.

124
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:37,879
<i>♪ Give my regards to Broadway ♪</i>

125
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:41,049
<i>♪ Remember me to Herald Square ♪</i>

126
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:42,300
Your turn!

127
00:05:42,383 --> 00:05:45,511
<i>♪ Something, something</i>
<i>Something, something, Broadway ♪</i>

128
00:05:45,595 --> 00:05:47,847
<i>♪ Old people seem to like this song! ♪</i>

129
00:05:47,930 --> 00:05:48,765
Big finish!

130
00:05:48,848 --> 00:05:51,100
<i>♪ Give my regards to old Broadway! ♪</i>

131
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:53,061
Gwen, stop encouraging her!

132
00:05:53,144 --> 00:05:54,645
But this is fun.

133
00:05:54,729 --> 00:05:57,148
She's high as a kite that's also on drugs.

134
00:05:57,231 --> 00:05:58,983
[laughs heartily]

135
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:01,069
Grandma, can you please just chill out?

136
00:06:01,152 --> 00:06:03,196
Boo!

137
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:06,783
-Yeah. Yeah. Boo!
-Boo!

138
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:11,120
-Wait. We just passed a tattoo shop. Stop!
-Forget it, Gwen.

139
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:14,916
My only job is to get her home safe.
Okay? I'm not stopping for anything.

140
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:16,793
-Red light!
-[brakes screech]

141
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:21,923
[exclaims, snorts]

142
00:06:22,006 --> 00:06:23,966
-[Kitty chuckles]
-Come on.

143
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:24,884
This is my chance.

144
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:27,387
Your grandma's out of it.
She'll sign the release.

145
00:06:27,887 --> 00:06:31,641
Right, Mrs. Forman?
You want me to get a tattoo, don't you?

146
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:35,978
Yeah. And then let's steal a boat
and go to Vegas.

147
00:06:36,062 --> 00:06:38,398
No. We're going home,
we're putting Grandma to bed,

148
00:06:38,481 --> 00:06:41,859
and we're showing my grandpa
that Jay is a responsible human being.

149
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:46,614
[rhythmic mouth noises]

150
00:06:52,537 --> 00:06:53,830
-Guess who?
-Oh my God!

151
00:06:53,913 --> 00:06:55,498
-[laughing]
-[Leia gasps] Oh my God!

152
00:06:55,581 --> 00:06:56,999
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh!

153
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:58,835
[laughing]

154
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:00,586
We'll be quick.

155
00:07:02,088 --> 00:07:02,964
Later, nerds.

156
00:07:03,798 --> 00:07:06,050
[rock music playing]

157
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:09,303
Nik?

158
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:11,139
[laughing] What?!

159
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:12,306
You?! Here?!

160
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:13,724
I mean, whoa!

161
00:07:13,808 --> 00:07:16,769
Now? How? What? Weird!

162
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,688
I told you I was gonna be here.

163
00:07:18,771 --> 00:07:20,440
Right. Right, with your tutor.

164
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:24,068
I totally forgot about him. Where is he?

165
00:07:24,152 --> 00:07:27,029
Oh, Trevor? Here he comes.

166
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:30,450
[seductive funk music playing]

167
00:07:37,582 --> 00:07:41,085
[in slow motion] Holy sh-- [bleeped]

168
00:07:42,753 --> 00:07:44,213
[music fades]

169
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:46,048
Trevor, this is my boyfriend, Nate.

170
00:07:46,549 --> 00:07:47,758
"Boyfriend"?

171
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:51,596
[snickering] More like "manfriend."
I can't grow any hair on my face,

172
00:07:51,679 --> 00:07:54,348
but from the waist down,
it is wall-to-wall carpeting.

173
00:07:55,766 --> 00:07:57,018
[in deep voice] And I'm Ozzie.

174
00:07:57,768 --> 00:08:00,605
My pediatrician said I'll be 6'2".

175
00:08:01,397 --> 00:08:03,774
-Oh. I've heard a lot about you.
-[Nate chuckles]

176
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:05,485
Nikki tells me
you're on the football team?

177
00:08:05,568 --> 00:08:06,944
Yeah, but we couldn't do it

178
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:09,489
without guys like you
in the stands cheering us on. So…

179
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:12,700
Actually, Trevor got
a football scholarship to Notre Dame.

180
00:08:12,783 --> 00:08:14,785
Not that he needs it.
His dad's a congressman.

181
00:08:15,369 --> 00:08:16,829
God bless America.

182
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:19,123
Well, this is fun.

183
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:21,000
And normal.

184
00:08:21,834 --> 00:08:24,545
Thanks for stopping by, but we really
need to get back to studying.

185
00:08:24,629 --> 00:08:28,216
Oh yeah. Super busy day on our end too.

186
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:32,470
Ozzie's… lizard is sick,
and I have to help with the pills.

187
00:08:34,263 --> 00:08:35,556
They go in the butt.

188
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:38,267
[chuckles] Okay, cool.

189
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:40,561
Nice to meet you, Nate.
Nice to meet you, Ozzie.

190
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:42,104
[in normal voice] I'm 25.

191
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:44,649
[laughs]

192
00:08:47,026 --> 00:08:47,860
You're screwed.

193
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:50,780
[Leia sighs]

194
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:52,281
[both] What's taking so long?

195
00:08:52,865 --> 00:08:55,326
Aw, we said that at the same time.
We're adorable.

196
00:08:55,409 --> 00:08:57,620
I can't do adorable right now.

197
00:08:57,703 --> 00:08:59,163
If your grandpa beats us home…

198
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:01,374
-He's…
-[both] Gonna kill us.

199
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:03,584
Okay, that was cute.

200
00:09:06,295 --> 00:09:07,380
Finally.

201
00:09:07,463 --> 00:09:09,590
-Let's see it.
-Oh, I bailed on the tattoo.

202
00:09:09,674 --> 00:09:11,842
Some lady cut in front of me,
and it was taking forever.

203
00:09:12,718 --> 00:09:13,970
I got a tattoo!

204
00:09:16,347 --> 00:09:17,348
To Vegas!

205
00:09:18,474 --> 00:09:21,060
[rock music playing]

206
00:09:21,852 --> 00:09:23,020
So I was right.

207
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:25,439
That Trevor dude is
obviously trying to seduce Nikki.

208
00:09:25,523 --> 00:09:27,733
I don't think he needs to try very hard.

209
00:09:29,318 --> 00:09:31,404
How am I gonna save my relationship?

210
00:09:31,487 --> 00:09:33,281
He's hot. He's smart.

211
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:35,116
He doesn't owe Nikki 70 bucks.

212
00:09:37,535 --> 00:09:38,494
I got it.

213
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:40,621
I'll go kick his ass. Duh!

214
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:42,498
So you're the "let's bring him out" guy.

215
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:43,416
The what guy?

216
00:09:43,499 --> 00:09:45,376
There's one on every talk show.

217
00:09:46,168 --> 00:09:48,337
The host says, "Let's bring him out."

218
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:49,589
Everyone boos.

219
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:52,008
Then he says, "You don't know me."

220
00:09:54,135 --> 00:09:56,053
Have you never seen a talk show?

221
00:09:57,138 --> 00:10:01,100
-[theme music plays]
-[audience chanting] Ozzie! Ozzie! Ozzie!

222
00:10:01,183 --> 00:10:03,102
Welcome back!

223
00:10:03,185 --> 00:10:06,397
Today, we have Nikki and Trevor.

224
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,857
[audience] Aww!

225
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,692
They may look like the perfect couple,

226
00:10:10,985 --> 00:10:13,195
but somebody has a problem with that.

227
00:10:14,363 --> 00:10:15,615
Let's bring him out.

228
00:10:15,698 --> 00:10:17,116
[theme music plays]

229
00:10:17,199 --> 00:10:18,492
[audience] Boo!

230
00:10:18,576 --> 00:10:21,412
Hey, you don't know me! You don't know me!

231
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:24,040
Nate.

232
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:26,792
Why don't you tell us
what's gotten you so upset?

233
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:30,588
That's my girlfriend,
and now she's hanging out with this chump,

234
00:10:30,671 --> 00:10:32,506
and suddenly I'm not good enough for her.

235
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:33,424
Nikki?

236
00:10:33,507 --> 00:10:37,928
Nate's fine, but… Trevor stimulates
my mind <i>and</i> my body.

237
00:10:38,012 --> 00:10:39,430
-[audience exclaims]
-Both?!

238
00:10:39,513 --> 00:10:40,598
That's impossible!

239
00:10:41,307 --> 00:10:42,266
Not for me.

240
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:43,768
[audience exclaiming]

241
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:45,895
Nate, stop.

242
00:10:45,978 --> 00:10:49,190
I'm done playing around.
Nik, you need to make a choice.

243
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:51,525
Is it him? Or is it me?

244
00:10:51,609 --> 00:10:52,693
Oh, then him.

245
00:10:53,277 --> 00:10:54,445
This guy?!

246
00:10:54,528 --> 00:10:55,696
You don't know him.

247
00:10:56,781 --> 00:10:57,823
You don't know him.

248
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:01,535
[audience exclaims]

249
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:03,120
Shut up! You don't know me!

250
00:11:03,204 --> 00:11:05,456
-[audience booing]
-You don't know me!

251
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:08,709
Nobody knows you.

252
00:11:10,419 --> 00:11:11,504
Stop saying that.

253
00:11:11,587 --> 00:11:14,840
-[theme music plays]
-[audience cheering]

254
00:11:16,425 --> 00:11:17,843
I need to talk to Nikki.

255
00:11:18,678 --> 00:11:22,056
-And what are you gonna say to her?
-This is getting weird, dude.

256
00:11:22,932 --> 00:11:24,141
We'll be right back.

257
00:11:25,893 --> 00:11:28,354
[rock music playing]

258
00:11:29,063 --> 00:11:30,398
A tattoo?!

259
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:33,234
I don't even wear waterproof mascara.

260
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:34,819
Red's gonna kill me.

261
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:35,903
Gwen.

262
00:11:35,986 --> 00:11:39,824
I know. But I stopped her
from getting a barbed wire tramp stamp.

263
00:11:39,907 --> 00:11:41,367
So you're welcome.

264
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:45,705
Grandma, I am so sorry.
None of this was supposed to happen.

265
00:11:45,788 --> 00:11:47,081
How are you cooking dinner now?

266
00:11:47,164 --> 00:11:51,585
It is helping me deal with the stress
of waking up with a flipping tattoo!

267
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:53,504
What's the emergency?

268
00:11:53,587 --> 00:11:56,132
D'you run out of eggs?
'Cause I don't know how that happened.

269
00:11:56,215 --> 00:11:58,175
Look what happened at the dentist.

270
00:11:58,259 --> 00:12:00,761
Holy crapola!

271
00:12:00,845 --> 00:12:04,265
I heard of them feeling you up
when you're out, but this crosses a line.

272
00:12:04,765 --> 00:12:06,809
My mother would be rolling in her grave,

273
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:08,978
if we hadn't spread her ashes

274
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:11,856
in the parking lot
of the Sizzler by her church.

275
00:12:13,149 --> 00:12:14,233
Did you get one too?

276
00:12:14,316 --> 00:12:16,444
You've been talking nonstop about tatties.

277
00:12:16,527 --> 00:12:19,196
No. You told me not to get one,
and I always follow what you tell me.

278
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:22,324
Good. Those things are
a one-way ticket to whore town.

279
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:25,244
Sorry.

280
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:28,080
Are you sure there is no way
to get this off?

281
00:12:28,164 --> 00:12:31,041
Is there a… a special cream or something?

282
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:33,794
If there was I wouldn't have
Fred Flintstone riding a surfboard

283
00:12:33,878 --> 00:12:35,004
on my hip bone.

284
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:36,756
[door shuts]

285
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:40,843
That's Red.
Good Lord, what is he gonna think?

286
00:12:40,926 --> 00:12:42,803
Oh man, he's gonna be pissed.

287
00:12:42,887 --> 00:12:45,681
Stomp around,
probably take away my allowance.

288
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:51,103
Sorry. It's a Dad flashback.

289
00:12:51,812 --> 00:12:52,980
You need to get out of here.

290
00:12:53,063 --> 00:12:55,357
No, I'm not leaving you here
to take the blame.

291
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:57,693
Cool. If he has
the blame thing covered, I'm out.

292
00:12:57,777 --> 00:12:59,195
Hang on.

293
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:02,031
Take these. We're low on fresh produce.

294
00:13:03,824 --> 00:13:05,367
[sighs] Don't let Grandpa see your wrist

295
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:07,244
until we figure out
the best way to tell him.

296
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:10,873
I do not keep things from my husband.
He is a reasonable man.

297
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:19,965
Down in hell,
there's this little room in the wayback

298
00:13:20,049 --> 00:13:23,594
where the devil craps fire
into your mouth.

299
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:29,099
That's the DMV.

300
00:13:31,977 --> 00:13:33,145
How was your day, dear?

301
00:13:34,021 --> 00:13:35,773
Oh, it was just… It was…

302
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:38,692
It… It was great.

303
00:13:39,318 --> 00:13:42,446
Just, like, nothing crazy happened.

304
00:13:43,739 --> 00:13:45,074
And what's he doing here?

305
00:13:45,157 --> 00:13:46,075
Um…

306
00:13:46,158 --> 00:13:49,537
He brought Grandma the chicken.
[chuckles] From his garden.

307
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:50,621
Yes.

308
00:13:50,704 --> 00:13:52,122
I was making supper.

309
00:13:54,583 --> 00:13:56,877
I… I have to get up inside there.

310
00:13:57,378 --> 00:13:58,921
Oh yeah.

311
00:13:59,421 --> 00:14:01,006
This is gonna be yummy.

312
00:14:03,717 --> 00:14:05,469
Wanna take that chicken off your hand?

313
00:14:06,846 --> 00:14:07,680
I do not.

314
00:14:10,975 --> 00:14:12,977
I'm gonna go get the laundry now.

315
00:14:18,816 --> 00:14:21,694
[rock music playing]

316
00:14:22,736 --> 00:14:25,531
I am so disappointed in you.

317
00:14:26,198 --> 00:14:27,366
All of you.

318
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:31,328
But especially you, little Kelso.

319
00:14:31,412 --> 00:14:33,581
I was wrong the other day.

320
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:37,418
You are a complete waste
of a foot in the ass.

321
00:14:38,252 --> 00:14:40,087
You never even gave him a chance.

322
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:43,340
You decided based on his last name
that you were going to hate him.

323
00:14:43,424 --> 00:14:44,466
This is so unfair.

324
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:46,594
And that's what makes it fun for me.

325
00:14:47,094 --> 00:14:48,095
Leia, he's right.

326
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:52,516
It is my fault, sir.
I was the one driving.

327
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:55,728
Look, I'm not proud of what happened,

328
00:14:55,811 --> 00:14:59,773
but I do believe the mistakes we make
are what turn us into the men we become.

329
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:03,861
And I would like to become a man
worthy of dating your granddaughter.

330
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:07,156
-Get out.
-Already gone.

331
00:15:07,823 --> 00:15:09,199
And you, go to your room.

332
00:15:09,283 --> 00:15:10,200
[door closes]

333
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:15,289
Red, don't you think
you're being a little harsh?

334
00:15:15,372 --> 00:15:17,833
Yeah, they made a mistake,
but nobody got hurt.

335
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:21,879
My wife is tatted up
like she's doing time at Rikers.

336
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,423
I'm starting to like it.

337
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:27,384
I feel like Rizzo from <i>Grease</i>.

338
00:15:29,386 --> 00:15:33,974
All I asked you to do
was to give Kitty a simple ride home.

339
00:15:34,058 --> 00:15:39,146
But you pawned it off on the kids
and turned it into a circus.

340
00:15:39,647 --> 00:15:41,231
Like everything in your life.

341
00:15:42,191 --> 00:15:43,192
You know what?

342
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:45,027
Screw you.

343
00:15:45,527 --> 00:15:46,403
[scoffs]

344
00:15:46,487 --> 00:15:47,905
You're such a blowhard.

345
00:15:47,988 --> 00:15:50,199
You know how many years
I spent getting yelled at,

346
00:15:50,282 --> 00:15:52,493
being told how much I messed up?

347
00:15:52,576 --> 00:15:56,372
So you don't have to respect me,
because I finally respect myself.

348
00:15:56,455 --> 00:16:00,042
And I don't have to stand here
while you yell at me anymore.

349
00:16:01,335 --> 00:16:04,546
And thanks a lot for never teaching me
how to ride a bike!

350
00:16:07,549 --> 00:16:09,218
Do I look like her father?

351
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:15,057
[Kitty sighs]

352
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:17,309
I brought you a little treat.

353
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:21,021
-What's with her?
-Oh, Red.

354
00:16:21,522 --> 00:16:22,982
Leia is a teenager.

355
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:26,527
She's bursting with hormones
and bad decisions.

356
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,362
I was talking about Sherri.

357
00:16:28,445 --> 00:16:31,907
Well, she's bursting with hormones
and bad decisions too.

358
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:34,535
I mean…

359
00:16:34,618 --> 00:16:39,456
If she has issues with her father,
let her go and yell at him.

360
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:40,499
Yeah.

361
00:16:40,582 --> 00:16:45,087
It's not great when people blame you
for other people's problems.

362
00:16:45,587 --> 00:16:46,714
[grumbles]

363
00:16:49,049 --> 00:16:49,883
What?

364
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:51,385
Jay is not his father.

365
00:16:52,636 --> 00:16:56,181
He could have run off,
let Leia take all the blame.

366
00:16:56,265 --> 00:16:59,727
But you saw how he stood up for her
and took responsibility.

367
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:01,562
Michael Kelso would never have done that.

368
00:17:01,645 --> 00:17:05,482
Michael Kelso glued himself
to our refrigerator.

369
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:09,236
I think you're setting the bar kinda low.

370
00:17:09,862 --> 00:17:12,364
Well, look, Red. I'm guilty of it too.

371
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:14,408
Leia's right.

372
00:17:14,491 --> 00:17:16,827
We never really did give Jay a chance.

373
00:17:18,162 --> 00:17:20,289
-[Red sighs]
-Oh, oh, oh, oh!

374
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:24,877
I know that sound.
It means you're starting to come around.

375
00:17:26,003 --> 00:17:28,589
While you're a little open-minded…

376
00:17:29,214 --> 00:17:30,049
Do you hate it?

377
00:17:31,091 --> 00:17:32,926
Well, actually…

378
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:36,221
-It's kind of adventurous.
-[Kitty giggles]

379
00:17:36,305 --> 00:17:37,681
[murmurs playfully]

380
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:40,225
Oh!

381
00:17:40,309 --> 00:17:42,186
I know what you're in the mood for.

382
00:17:42,269 --> 00:17:43,812
Yeah. [chuckles]

383
00:17:45,481 --> 00:17:46,607
Yeah!

384
00:17:52,529 --> 00:17:53,530
[Nikki] Hey, babe.

385
00:17:56,658 --> 00:17:57,701
Are you okay?

386
00:17:57,785 --> 00:18:00,454
You didn't squeeze my butt
and say, "Hey, ladies."

387
00:18:01,497 --> 00:18:04,541
Nik, I'm kind of freaking out about us.

388
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:07,211
-You've been spending time with Trevor--
-Trevor?

389
00:18:07,294 --> 00:18:09,671
Nate, there's nothing
between me and Trevor.

390
00:18:09,755 --> 00:18:11,340
You know I don't like muscular guys.

391
00:18:13,342 --> 00:18:15,219
I don't know how I feel about that, but…

392
00:18:15,886 --> 00:18:19,181
It's not just him.
It's all this other stuff.

393
00:18:19,264 --> 00:18:20,933
The SATs, the studying.

394
00:18:22,601 --> 00:18:24,603
I'm afraid you're gonna leave me behind.

395
00:18:24,686 --> 00:18:27,022
Nate, I'm not going to college
to leave you behind.

396
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:30,275
I'm… I'm going to college
so I can have a future.

397
00:18:31,610 --> 00:18:32,736
Am I in that future?

398
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,613
Well, the future's not set.

399
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:37,449
There's no fate
but what we make for ourselves.

400
00:18:38,158 --> 00:18:39,993
You're hot <i>and </i>you quote <i>Terminator 2!</i>

401
00:18:41,703 --> 00:18:43,872
I can't imagine not being with you.

402
00:18:45,415 --> 00:18:47,876
I need you to tell me
we're always gonna be together.

403
00:18:48,669 --> 00:18:49,670
Hey, come here.

404
00:18:52,339 --> 00:18:56,260
Babe, I don't know what's gonna happen.
All I know is that I love you.

405
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:58,428
And I hope that's enough.

406
00:18:59,763 --> 00:19:00,722
It is.

407
00:19:05,644 --> 00:19:07,855
-Feeling better?
-Yeah.

408
00:19:09,064 --> 00:19:10,732
Hello, ladies. [chuckles]

409
00:19:12,151 --> 00:19:14,444
Okay, well I have to head home for dinner.

410
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:17,281
-Are you sure you're okay?
-Yeah.

411
00:19:17,364 --> 00:19:19,700
-Yeah, totally.
-Okay.

412
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:23,954
[melancholic rock music playing]

413
00:19:24,663 --> 00:19:25,706
[knocking]

414
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:29,376
Hey there.

415
00:19:29,459 --> 00:19:32,087
Listen, kiddo. I've been thinking.

416
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:34,965
If you really want to see this Kelso kid,

417
00:19:36,675 --> 00:19:37,718
I'll give him a chance.

418
00:19:38,927 --> 00:19:39,761
Really?

419
00:19:40,762 --> 00:19:43,724
But you gotta be careful.
No more joyrides.

420
00:19:43,807 --> 00:19:46,768
And he's not allowed upstairs. Fair?

421
00:19:47,769 --> 00:19:50,647
So fair. I'll tell Jay everything
the next time I see him.

422
00:19:50,731 --> 00:19:51,732
Uh-huh.

423
00:19:57,863 --> 00:19:58,864
Already gone.

424
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:01,200
[Leia and Jay] Bye, babe!

425
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:02,576
[both] Aww!

426
00:20:04,369 --> 00:20:07,206
[rock music playing]

427
00:20:08,081 --> 00:20:10,292
I talked to Kitty, and I gotta tell ya,

428
00:20:11,126 --> 00:20:12,336
I know you're not my dad.

429
00:20:14,087 --> 00:20:15,756
For one thing, you're alive.

430
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:18,842
And also you're not a jerk.

431
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:24,848
Well, uh, are we here to chat or…
or learn?

432
00:20:24,932 --> 00:20:26,934
Now… like we practiced.

433
00:20:27,017 --> 00:20:29,561
[Sherri exhales]
My balance is probably pretty good

434
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:32,439
from all those times
I walked home drunk in high heels.

435
00:20:33,815 --> 00:20:36,109
Oh, I'm doing it! I'm doing it!

436
00:20:36,193 --> 00:20:38,528
All right, there you go. Now turn around.

437
00:20:38,612 --> 00:20:39,529
Hey, I'm doing it.

438
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:40,656
Good job.

439
00:20:41,573 --> 00:20:44,451
-Now, brake. Okay, now brake.
-Oh, whoa! [screams]

440
00:20:44,534 --> 00:20:45,535
[crashing]

441
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:46,828
[Red] You idiot!

442
00:20:46,912 --> 00:20:48,413
[Sherri] Don't worry. I'm okay.

443
00:20:48,497 --> 00:20:51,416
[rock music playing]

